         <div type="translation">
            <p>Sophrone.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Transcription from Richter (1956 [1920]). Sophrone was probably the owner of the ring
                    and the woman depicted. The headress was common in the time of Hadrian's rule
                    (117-138 CE), while the shape of the ringstone was more common the third century
                    CE. </p>
         </div>
